JavaScript Practical Questions

Create an input box and a button. When the button is clicked, display the entered name inside a paragraph using innerHTML.

Take the user's name from an input box and display the message "Hello <name>, Welcome!" inside a div using innerHTML.

Create a paragraph and a button "Make Text Red". When the button is clicked, change the color of the paragraph text to red using JavaScript style.

Take age from an input box and display "Your age is: <age>" inside a span using innerHTML.

Create a button "Change Background". When the button is clicked, change the background color of the page using JavaScript style.

Take First Name and Last Name from two input fields and display the full name inside a paragraph using innerHTML.

Create a paragraph and two buttons "Increase Size" and "Decrease Size". Change the paragraph font size using JavaScript style.

Take a color name from an input box and display the text "Your favorite color is <color>". Also change the text color to the same color using style.

Create a paragraph and two buttons "Hide Text" and "Show Text". Hide and show the paragraph using style.display.

Take two numbers from input boxes and display their sum inside a paragraph using innerHTML.
